def: The district, office, or residence of an archdeacon. SeeBenefice.Every diocese is divided into archdeaconries. Blackstone.
Leprous; infectious; corrupting; poisonous. "The leperousdistillment." Shak.
The quality of being extraordinary. [R.] Gov. of the Tongue.
The science of method or arrangement; a treatise on method.Coleridge.
Destitute of mercy; cruel; unsparing; -- said of animatebeings, and also, figuratively, of things; as, a merciless tyrant;merciless waves.The foe is merciless, and will not pity. Shak.
The state of being healthy or healthful; freedom from disease.
To surpass (Herod) in violence or wickedness; to exceed in anyvicious or offensive particular. "It out-Herods Herod." Shak.Out-Heroding the preposterous fashions of the times. Sir W. Scott.
One of two Roman officers or magistrates united in the samepublic functions.

Passing through the different stages in its life history on analternation of hosts, as the common wheat-rust fungus (Pucciniagraminis), and certain other parasitic fungi; -- contrasted withautocious. -- Het`er*o"cism (#), n.
